{{Not to be confused with|May 14|qq=May 14}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月十四|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 14일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 14''' is the 14th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Jōkyū|Jōkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1221]] [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – In the incident known as [[:en:Jōkyū War|Jōkyū no Ran]], the forces of the Kamakura shogunate, seeking to overthrow the regime, were assembled by {{ill|Go-Toba†Go-Toba_Tennō|ja|後鳥羽上皇|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Go-Toba†Go-Toba_Tennō|qq=}} along with approximately 1700 samurai from neighboring provinces. * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1839]] [[:en:June 24|June 24]]) – In the event known as the [[:en:Bansha no goku|Bansha no Goku]], figures such as [[:en:Watanabe Kazan|Watanabe Kōzan]] and [[:en:Takano Chōei|Takano Chōei]] were arrested. * [[:en:Genji era|Genji]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1864]] [[:en:June 17|June 17]]) – The Tokugawa shogunate established the Kobe Naval Training Center, appointing [[:en:Katsu Kaishū|Katsu Kaishū]] as its head.
== Births == * [[Antei]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1227]] [[:en:June 29|June 29]]) – [[:en:Hōjō Tokiyori|Hojo Tokiyori]], the 5th shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (died [[1263]]). * [[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1793]] [[:en:June 22|June 22]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyoshi|Tokugawa Iekei]], the 12th shōgun of the Tokugawa shogunate (died [[1853]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 16th year (leap May) ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1588]] [[:en:July 7|July 7]]) – [[:en:Sassa Narimasa|Sasasa Narimasa]], a military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|武将|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|qq=}}) (born [[1516]]). * [[Keichō]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1606]] [[:en:June 19|June 19]]) – [[:en:Sakakibara Yasumasa|Sakakibara Yasumasa]], a military commander and one of the Tokugawa Four Heavenly Kings (born [[1548]]). <“{{ill|Tokugawa Tsuneyoshi|ja|徳川綱教|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa Tsuneyoshi|qq=}}” has a note stating “May 18” in another account.> == Commemorations == == See Also == {{Lunar Calendar See Also|5|13|5|15|4|14|6|5|0514|qq=}}
