'''May 14''' is the 14th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|1=Shakkō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11635368}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Jōkyū|en|Jōkyū|qid=Q1195428|lt=Jōkyū|1=Jōkyū}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1221|en|1221|qid=Q5393|lt=1221|1=1221}} {{ill|June 5|en|June 5|qid=Q2622|lt=June 5|1=June 5}}) – In the incident known as {{ill|Jōkyū War|en|Jōkyū War|qid=Q1372308|lt=Jōkyū no Ran|1=Jōkyū War}}, the forces of the Kamakura shogunate, seeking to overthrow the regime, were assembled by {{ill|Go-Toba†Go-Toba_Tennō|ja|後鳥羽上皇|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Go-Toba†Go-Toba_Tennō|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 後鳥羽天皇|1=Emperor Go-Toba|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q316658}} along with approximately 1700 samurai from neighboring provinces.
* {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenpō|1=Tenpō}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1839|en|1839|qid=Q7616|lt=1839|1=1839}} {{ill|June 24|en|June 24|qid=Q2665|lt=June 24|1=June 24}}) – In the event known as the {{ill|Bansha no goku|en|Bansha no goku|qid=Q2883476|lt=Bansha no Goku|1=Bansha no goku}}, figures such as {{ill|Watanabe Kazan|en|Watanabe Kazan|qid=Q3130609|lt=Watanabe Kōzan|1=Watanabe Kazan}} and {{ill|Takano Chōei|en|Takano Chōei|qid=Q944693|lt=Takano Chōei|1=Takano Chōei}} were arrested.
* {{ill|Genji era|en|Genji era|qid=Q1325419|lt=Genji|1=Genji era}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1864|en|1864|qid=Q7704|lt=1864|1=1864}} {{ill|June 17|en|June 17|qid=Q2672|lt=June 17|1=June 17}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate established the Kobe Naval Training Center, appointing {{ill|Katsu Kaishū|en|Katsu Kaishū|qid=Q700470|lt=Katsu Kaishū|1=Katsu Kaishū}} as its head.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Antei|en|Antei|qid=Q737537|lt=Antei|1=Antei}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1227|en|1227|qid=Q5407|lt=1227|1=1227}} {{ill|June 29|en|June 29|qid=Q2659|lt=June 29|1=June 29}}) – {{ill|Hōjō Tokiyori|en|Hōjō Tokiyori|qid=Q1354410|lt=Hojo Tokiyori|1=Hōjō Tokiyori}}, the 5th shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (died {{ill|1263|en|1263|qid=Q5512|lt=1263|1=1263}}).
* {{ill|Kansei|en|Kansei|qid=Q1195131|lt=Kansei|1=Kansei}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1793|en|1793|qid=Q7807|lt=1793|1=1793}} {{ill|June 22|en|June 22|qid=Q2663|lt=June 22|1=June 22}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyoshi|en|Tokugawa Ieyoshi|qid=Q439675|lt=Tokugawa Iekei|1=Tokugawa Ieyoshi}}, the 12th shōgun of the Tokugawa shogunate (died {{ill|1853|en|1853|qid=Q7666|lt=1853|1=1853}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|en|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qid=Q1145058|lt=Tenshō Era|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 16th year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1588|en|1588|qid=Q6757|lt=1588|1=1588}} {{ill|July 7|en|July 7|qid=Q2694|lt=July 7|1=July 7}}) – {{ill|Sassa Narimasa|en|Sassa Narimasa|qid=Q1186700|lt=Sasasa Narimasa|1=Sassa Narimasa}}, a military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|武将|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|1=military commander|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11545923}}) (born {{ill|1516|en|1516|qid=Q6212|lt=1516|1=1516}}).
* {{ill|Keichō|en|Keichō|qid=Q1328185|lt=Keichō|1=Keichō}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1606|en|1606|qid=Q6747|lt=1606|1=1606}} {{ill|June 19|en|June 19|qid=Q2669|lt=June 19|1=June 19}}) – {{ill|Sakakibara Yasumasa|en|Sakakibara Yasumasa|qid=Q1062738|lt=Sakakibara Yasumasa|1=Sakakibara Yasumasa}}, a military commander and one of the Tokugawa Four Heavenly Kings (born {{ill|1548|en|1548|qid=Q6551|lt=1548|1=1548}}).
